    base:desc "The twin operates on a 100 ms clock synchronization accuracy, mandated by safety‑critical vehicular standards, to support computation off‑loading among devices. A temporal granularity of 100 ms is the baseline for all digital‑physical interactions, ensuring that sensor data, control commands, and model updates are exchanged within this bound. Latency requirements are implicit in maintaining this 100 ms window, with any communication or processing delays exceeding this bound considered unacceptable for real‑time vehicle control."
